cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on the challenges faced by a robot in real-life applications and introduces a dataset collected with an RGB-D camera mounted on a mobile robot. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper evaluates the performance of deep convolutional networks on the new dataset and analyzes the transferability of deep representations from Web images to robotic data. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the lack of good visual perceptual systems for robots and the need for autonomous agents in real-world applications. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep convolutional networks for object recognition and analyzes the transferability of deep representations. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper introduces a large-scale, multi-view object dataset collected with an RGB-D camera mounted on a mobile robot, which can be considered as multimedia data.
